result.execSummary:
The defendant Christian G. Cerney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Issue of Worthless Checks(<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.24(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Restitution in the amount of $707.00 paid directly to the Clerk of Court's Office prior to sentencing.  The 10% surcharge in the amount of $70.70 still due and owing - same repayment conditions apply as noted below for the Costs.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

Case called @ 2:00 p.m. Defendant Christian G. Cerney in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. No statement by DE. Court orders: Restitution in the amount of $707.00, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights given.

Case Called @ 1:33 PM: Defendant Christian G. Cerney in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court questions Def as to status of counsel with SPD.  Def states he was not found eligible for SPD services.  Def requests that counsel be appointed by the Court.  Court suggests an alternative to Def on speaking directly with the DA's office prior to deciding on counsel issue.  Def would like to speak with the State on his own.  Off Record for Def to speak directly with ADA.  Back of Record at 1:40 PM:   Per DA - case is on track to resolution.  Def wishes to pay Restitution in full.  State requests adjournment of approx 60 days to allow for payment.  Def confirms State's recital and requests the add'l time of 3 mos.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for February 8, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
Defendant is prohibited from issuing any checks for payment.    Complete ID process with the Sheriff's Department.

Case Called @ 1:38 PM: Defendant Christian G. Cerney in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def wants counsel.  Has no funds to retain his own counsel - currently disabled on SSI/VI benefits.  Def referred to SPD for eligibility process.  NGP entered by Court.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for November 17, 2015 at 01:45 pm.
